Title: Illuminated Incipit
Medium: ink and pigments on buff European wove paper
Description: This illuminated incipit page from Walters manuscript W.66a has an unusually designed headpiece comprised of a star and crescent with flags, two trumpets, and a drum.
Keywords: Islamic; Ottoman; Turkish; Book; Codex; Illustration; Manuscript; Contemporary Binding; Turkey; Science
Provenance: Henry Walters, Baltimore [date and mode of acquisition unknown]; Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.
Creator: Ahmed 'Ata Tayyarzade (died 1294 AH/AD 1877)
